# OmniLab Stripe Billing - environment configuration
# ===================================================
# Generated by stripe_billing.py (CRE-21) on first deploy.
#
# CURRENT STATE: placeholder/test values. Endpoints will return 503 until
# real Stripe keys are set. Webhook is reachable but skips signature check.
#
# WHEN THE REAL STRIPE ACCOUNT IS READY (a few days from now):
#   1. Log into https://dashboard.stripe.com (Test mode toggle on first)
#   2. Developers -> API keys -> copy publishable + secret keys (sk_test_, pk_test_)
#   3. Products -> create "OmniLab Pro Monthly" ($12/mo) and
#      "OmniLab Pro Yearly" ($99/yr). Copy each Price ID (starts price_).
#   4. Developers -> Webhooks -> Add endpoint:
#         URL:     https://omnilab.io/api/billing/webhook   (or your test URL)
#         Events:  checkout.session.completed, invoice.payment_failed
#      Then copy the Signing secret (whsec_).
#   5. Replace the four <REPLACE_*> values below.
#   6. Restart backend.
#   7. To go LIVE: flip Dashboard to Live mode, regenerate keys (sk_live_,
#      pk_live_), recreate products in Live mode (new price IDs), update
#      this file, restart.

# --- Stripe API keys ---
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=<REPLACE_WITH_sk_test_FROM_DASHBOARD>
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=<REPLACE_WITH_pk_test_FROM_DASHBOARD>

# --- Webhook signing secret ---
# Get this from Developers -> Webhooks -> click your endpoint -> Signing secret
# Until set, the webhook will accept events WITHOUT signature verification.
# That's fine for local testing with `stripe listen`, NOT OK for production.
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=<REPLACE_WITH_whsec_FROM_DASHBOARD>

# --- Price IDs (one per plan) ---
# Create products in Stripe Dashboard -> Products. Each product gets one or
# more Prices; the Price ID is what goes here (NOT the product ID).
STRIPE_PRICE_MONTHLY=<REPLACE_WITH_price_FOR_$12_MONTHLY>
STRIPE_PRICE_YEARLY=<REPLACE_WITH_price_FOR_$99_YEARLY>

# --- Return URLs after checkout ---
# These point at OmniLab pages users see post-payment / on cancel.
# For local dev: http://localhost:5000/... is fine.
# For prod: change to https://omnilab.io/...
STRIPE_SUCCESS_URL=http://localhost:5000/checkout/success
STRIPE_CANCEL_URL=http://localhost:5000/checkout/cancel
